step.tex:
\text{Number of elements} = 3\times 3 = 9\\
\text{and each element} \in \{0, \;1\}\\
\implies 2^9 = 512 \text{ possible matrices}

\text{Number of elements} = 3\times 3 = 9\\
\text{and each element} \in \{0, \;1\}\\
\implies 9^2 =  81 \text{ possible matrices}

step.reason:
\text{The number of possible matrices}= k^n \text{ where,}\\
k = \text{ set of values that each element can take}\\
\text{and n} = \text{ number of elements in the matrix.}
